The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Calcutta, April 27: Polaris Software Lab will buy back its shares of Rs 5 each up to 10 per cent of the total paid-up capital and free reserves as on March 31. However, the buyback amount will not exceed 25 per cent of the paid-up capital. The mode of purchase will be from open market through stock exchanges at a price not exceeding Rs 115 per share payable in cash. The total buyback amount, however, will not exceed Rs 49 crore.

 Hyderabad, April 27: IVRCL Infrastructures amp; Projects Ltd (IVRCL) will acquire 70 per cent of Hindustan Dorr-Oliver (HDL) shares at a consideration of Rs 53.90 crore. The company will buy out the stock from Jumbo World Holdings Ltd.

 Mumbai, April 27: IL amp;FS Investsmart Ltd has filed a draft red herring prospectus with the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) for a book-built initial public offering (IPO) of 11.4 million shares.

 New Delhi, April 27: Infrastructure Development Finance Co (IDFC) will come out with an IPO by June and set up a second infrastructure fund of Rs 1,300 crore in eight to nine months. The company has registered a net profit of Rs 304 crore in 2004-05 against Rs 259 crore last year. 

 Chennai, April 27: Indian Overseas Bank will raise Rs 250 crore from a GDR issue, probably by June end. ?We have decided to take the GDR route to raise Rs 250 crore by offering 7 crore shares,? chairman S. C. Gupta said.

 Beijing, April 27: Chinas Shanghai Baosteel group, and Maanshan Iron and Steel Co plan to buy more iron ore from India to diversify supply and reduce costs after prices of the raw material rose to a record.

 London, April 27: Indian garment exports to the 25-nation European Union may increase in the coming months. This is due to EU?s decision to launch an investigation into nine categories of Chinese exports, seven of them related to clothing.




